55.7	Plasmodium	Plasmodium	Plasmodium is a genus of parasitic protists. Infection by these organisms is known as malaria. The genus Plasmodium was described in 1885 by Ettore Marchiafava and Angelo Celli. Currently over 200 species of this genus are recognized and new species continue to be described.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f1/Malaria.jpg/220px-Malaria.jpg
